    "text": "I sure will. [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] This is a document dated January 26, 1926. And it states that Miss Gertrud Kramer, who is my mother, applied to be converted to Judaism, and that she was accepted and she was given the name Ruth. And it is signed by the rabbi for the Jewish community in Berlin. This is a document issued by the Nazis in 1935, and bestowing on my father, Edmund Lehmann, an honorary cross or whatever you want to call this for his services during World War I. This is a document showing our registration with the American Consulate in Berlin for our application to immigrate to the United States.",
